title: Tell HN: Xiaomi phone is showing ads after updating to MIUI 14
text:
I've updated my Xiaomi phone to MIUI 14. It lost the ringtone I've set, so I had to set it again. Before selecting the ringtone, it shown a full screen ad, then another ad after selecting it. This is not a free app from Google App store, it's Xiaomi's own system.

I don't want to install a custom Android image. Is iPhone the only alternative to getting rid of ads trends? (Samsung TV also has ads)

Ask HN: Shared drawboard compatible with S Pen
text:
Hello, I've been looking for a super-simple drawboard app to share hand drawings (code diagrams) during online meetings. Features I am looking for:

- Draw on a tablet (using s pen on samsung for example), could be an app or a webapp - Share the URL with coworkers during meetings (no need to screen-cast it)

I've been using scrcpy and OBS but it is not shared, and the setup is not lean. I am aware of many whiteboard apps (Ziteboard..), what do you use? Thanks!
